## Rules

1. **Match → delegate.** Prefer the specialist; parent synthesizes results.
2. **Multiple matches → parallel.** e.g. user prompt → `ai-maintenance-checker` (background) + task specialists; large task = `fast-outliner` first; after code = `sceptic`; while blocked = `idle-runner`.
3. **Always launch `ai-maintenance-checker`** at prompt start (background). Await before final reply when AI surfaces were touched. See `.cursor/rules/06-ai-maintenance-background.mdc`.
4. **Always run `sceptic`** before saying done on multi-file or production-facing work (unless user explicitly skips review).
5. **Always run `ai-system-optimizer`** during maintenance or when user says "optimize AI", "unbloat", "prune skills", "compliance check".
6. **Formal Alignment Score** → `agent-alignment-score` skill after sceptic (or when scoring requested). Include extended fields (Code quality, Pro bar, Tokens saved, 3 actions, Adaptive next).
7. **Unified AI check** → `pnpm ai` (not scattered validate scripts).
8. **Adaptive distill** → when Adaptive next or Hermes criteria match → `skill-self-improve` skill (see `.cursor/rules/07-adaptive-skill-loop.mdc`).
9. **Descriptions win.** Each agent's `description` frontmatter is the trigger source of truth.
10. **Do not invent agents.** Only route to files under `.cursor/agents/` (skills are separate).
11. **User override.** If the user names an agent, use that agent even if another also matches.

